    {
      "id": "1904750c-f3ba-807e-98bd-fd09833ad7fd",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Group composition is a problem that is widely discussed in collaborative learning scenarios. The authors compare different approaches to grouping students in a face-to-face scenario. Grouping is done on an ontology-base and options are homogenous, heterogenous and random. Authors measure the activity levels and have students peer-review their work.",
